OL,3,CGovernment wins welfare vote but faces
OL,4,Cbiggest rebellion yet despite
OL,5,Cconcessions
OL,7,FThe government won a vote on its
OL,8,Fcontroversial, watered down welfare
OL,9,Fbill on Tuesday night - but faced its
OL,10,Fbiggest backbench rebellion so far.
OL,12,FThe Universal Credit and Personal
OL,13,FIndependence Payment Bill passed by
OL,14,F335 votes to 260. A total of 49 Labour
OL,15,FMP's rebelled against their own
OL,16,Fgovernment.
