OL,7,FThe next stage of the legislative
OL,8,Fprocess is called the committee stage,
OL,9,Fwhere MPs go through line-by-line
OL,10,Fexamination of the Bill.
OL,12,FMPs will then vote on the Bill for a
OL,13,Fthird and final time on July 9 - but
OL,14,Fmany Labour MPs have raised concerns
OL,15,Fthat doesn't leave enough time for
OL,16,Fproper scrutiny.
OL,18,FThe legislation then goes to the House
OL,19,Fof Lords, where further amendments can
OL,20,Fbe put forward before going back to
OL,21,Fthe Commons for approval.
